1. Videla sam *zmiju* u bašti. (*zmiju* - noun, subject) (I saw a snake in the garden.)
2. Zbog straha od *zmija*, ne mogu da uđem u šumu. (*zmija* - noun, object) (Because of fear of snakes, I cannot enter the forest.)
3. Uglavnom su *zmije* aktivne noću. (*zmije* - noun, subject) (Usually, snakes are active at night.)
4. *Zmijа* se polako približavala mišu. (*Zmija* - noun, subject) (The snake slowly approached the mouse.)
5. Kada sam ugledala *zmiju*, sledila sam se. (*zmiju* - noun, object) (When I saw the snake, I was frozen with fear.)
6. U zoološkom vrtu možete videti različite vrste *zmija*. (*zmija* - noun, object) (In the zoo, you can see different types of snakes.)
7. Zabrinut sam jer je moj pas ugrizao *zmiju*. (*zmiju* - noun, object) (I'm worried because my dog bit a snake.)
8. Čula sam da postoji mit da *zmije* ne mogu da čuju zvukove. (*zmije* - noun, subject) (I heard that there is a myth that snakes cannot hear sounds.)
9. *Zmijа* je iznenada iskočila ispred mene. (*Zmija* - noun, subject) (The snake suddenly jumped in front of me.)
10. Ne dirajte *zmije*, jer mogu da budu veoma opasne. (*zmije* - noun, subject) (Don't touch snakes because they can be very dangerous.)